# 15. 大切だから

Luka: Ichika, is something the matter?
Ichika: Huh? Why do you ask?
Luka: I detect a note of uncertainty in your guitar playing and singing.
Ichika: .....
Ichika: Luka, do you mind if I ask you for advice on something personal?
Luka: Not at all.
Ichika: I have a friend who's really important to me, and I want to respect her choices, but by doing that, I also feel like I'm failing her...
Ichika: I have no idea what to do.
Luka: And what are your feelings?
Ichika: Huh?
Luka: What do you wish for?
Ichika: I want to do what's right for everyone...
Luka: You know, there's no right or wrong in music.
Ichika: ...What?
Luka: It's down to individual interpretation.
Luka: Everyone brings their own tune to the table. Think of how you and your friends could put your tunes together into a beautiful melody.
Ichika: A melody for all of us...
Saki: Morning...
Shiho: Hi. Are you okay, Saki? You look kinda pale, and you've got bags under your eyes.
Saki: Whaaat, really? Haha, no need to worry. I stayed up late thinking about stuff, that's why.
Ichika: You worried about something?
Saki: I was just wondering whether we should tell Hona that we won't bother her about joining anymore.
Shiho: Seems unnecessary. We just won't ask her again.
Saki: No, but with how she is, I think she'll be agonizing over it unless we tell her we've given up.
Shiho: Saki...
Saki: So, it's best that we let her know our decision!
Ichika: Ah...
Saki: Hona! Sorry to interrupt your lunch break, but do you have a minute?
Honami: Oh, Saki...
Honami: I'm sorry, but... I was going to have lunch with some friends...
Saki: I won't take much of your time! And I won't ever bother you again, I promise!
Honami: ...What?
Saki: I'm sorry for being so insistent, asking you to join our band again and again.
Saki: I really wanted to find something that would bring the four of us together again, you know.
Saki: But I didn't realize how selfish I was being. I didn't consider it from your point of view. I'm really sorry.
Honami: You don't have to apologize!
Saki: Ichi told me everything. About what you went through in junior high school.
Saki: If something like that happened to me, I don't know how I'd have coped. It must have been so awful for you.
Saki: That's why I don't want to get between you and the friends you have now.
Honami: Oh, Saki...
Saki: So, that's all I wanted to say. Thanks for listening, and sorry for earlier.
Honami: It's okay...
Saki: I'll leave now! Bye, Hona!
Shiho: Do you think she's okay? We should've gone with her....
Ichika: .....
Shiho: Oh, she's back.
Saki: Hey, guys! Sorry to keep you waiting!
Ichika: How did it go? Did you tell her?
Saki: Yeah! I told her everything... Oh... Sorry...
Saki: I don't know why I'm crying... Haha... The tears just won't stop for some reason...
Ichika: .....
Shiho: Are you sure you're okay with giving up on Honami?
Saki: Yeah! I want what's best for her. And this is it.
Saki: We won't be hanging out together, but at least I can always walk by her classroom and look in to see how she's doing!
Ichika: Saki...
Saki: Oh, shoot. The lunch break is almost over and we haven't eaten lunch yet!
Shiho: .....
Shiho: Saki hasn't been herself ever since she spoke to Honami.
Ichika: ...Yeah.
Ichika: Do you think it really was for the best?
Shiho: You kidding?
Shiho: Nothing's ever felt more wrong.
